4th March 1949

Dear Mrs. White,

Many thanks for your charming letter. As you see, I have been very meek (though I also said "Jesus!" a few times as Ross1 did) and have omitted or changed some of the "long" words.2 I do hope that you will be able to retain a few things in the beginning, especially the last letters of the alphabet and the reference to the Maertz dictionary. The point is that this New Yorker issue will certainly be quoted by psychologists interested in colored hea